  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the position of a single font variation axis.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` pairs a four-byte axis tag with a floating-point design value to select a specific position along one axis of a variable font. An array of coordinates is passed to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate})> or used via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments> to instantiate the desired variation.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700f },
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth"), Value = 75f },
};
using var variantTypeface = typeface.Clone(coords);
```
]]></format></remarks>
